        mc"(Holy shit‚Ä¶ Trisha just came on to me in a not so subtle way. What is she expecting from me?)"
        show sc w3sowtlivingroom l23
        mc"(Why is she acting like this? And why did I find it so hard to resist her?)"
        show sc w3sowtlivingroom l22
        mc"(Dammit, I can hear [c_name]'s footsteps, she's on her way in here, so I better act naturally and hope that this erection isn‚Äôt easy to notice‚Ä¶!)"

    else:
        play sound "sound effects/01/00/door_opening_sound effect.mp3"
        show sc w3sowtlivingroom l05
        tri"OH! I think that might be [c_name] now."
        show sc w3sowtlivingroom l01
        tri"Um... I‚Äôm gonna go to my bedroom now and get changed as I have someone that I need to go and see."
        show sc w3sowtlivingroom l03
        tri"Have fun with my daughter [y_name]. See you soon‚Ä¶"
        mc"Okay Trisha, see you soon."
    if _in_replay:
        scene black
        with dissolve
        scene black
        with Pause (2)
    $ persistent.replay_w3_sow_trisha_house = False
    $ renpy.end_replay()
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)




label lb_w3sow_connie_upset:
    # Week 3 (SOW)  Scene 10 - The Boss' Daughter gets upset with her father over her birthday plans"
    scene sc w3sowbk k20
    with dissolve
    bw"So Connie, you must be pretty excited for your eighteenth birthday party?"
    show sc w3sowbk k23
    con"I seriously can‚Äôt wait Mom! It‚Äôs going to the best night ever."
    show sc w3sowbk k20
    bw"You‚Äôve had so many of your friends RSVP for it already."
    bw"It‚Äôs great that you‚Äôve made so many friends since you‚Äôve been at school."
    show sc w3sowbk k08
    con"Did you order everything I asked for Dad, like the balloons, the pink decorations, and the entertainment?"
    show sc w3sowbk k03
    tb"It‚Äôs all been taken care of. Only the best for my angel."
    show sc w3sowbk k08
    con"And where exactly are we having my party?"
    show sc w3sowbk k07
    con"You‚Äôve been very secretive about it, so I imagine that it must be somewhere very special in Sunshine Bay."
    show sc w3sowbk k09
    con"So, where is it going to be at?"
    show sc w3sowbk k01
    tb"Okay, just hear me out with this idea honey."
    # (TB leans in close to his daughter for this next line)"
    show sc w3sowbk k03
    tb"How would feel if we had your eighteenth birthday party at my hotel, in the penthouse suite?"
    show sc w3sowbk k10
    con"The penthouse suite? But‚Ä¶ It doesn‚Äôt have a pool up there?"
    show sc w3sowbk k02
    tb"Of course it doesn‚Äôt."
    show sc w3sowbk k03
    tb"What it has is an awesome view of the beach, three hundred and sixty-degree views of the town and surrounding suburbs..."
    tb"And I‚Äôve ordered the most incredible cake that you could possibly imagine!"
    # (Connie gets angry)"
    show sc w3sowbk k11
    con"But Dad, I specifically told you that I wanted a pool party for my birthday!"
    con"Can you please change it?"
    show sc w3sowbk k02
    tb"I‚Äôm sorry honey, but I can‚Äôt change it now, not with less than a week‚Äôs notice. Everything has already been paid for."
    tb"Besides, this party will mean a lot for the hotel."
    tb"Our business is not doing so well, so we need this party to happen in my hotel honey."
    show sc w3sowbk k03
    tb"The penthouse suite has an incredible view of the beach, especially at sunset."
    #(The boss closes his eyes and starts daydreaming)
    show sc w3sowbk k25
    tb"Imagine how much publicity and fame the hotel will have after your party sweetheart."
    tb"It‚Äôs the best decision from a business perspective."
    show sc w3sowbk k26
    con"Oh my God!"
    show sc w3sowbk k24
    con"I can‚Äôt believe you would do this. How could be so selfish??"
    con"All you care about is your stupid hotel!"
    show sc w3sowbk k02
    tb"Connie, you know that isn‚Äôt true."
    show sc w3sowbk k24
    con"Well if you don‚Äôt change it to a pool party for my birthday, then I won‚Äôt be there for it on Saturday!"
    show sc w3sowbk k02
    tb"Okay, now you‚Äôre overreacting."
    show sc w3sowbk k27
    con"I can‚Äôt believe you would do this to me! I hate you!!"
    # (Connie storms off and out of the house)"
    bw"Connie! Sweetheart!"
    # (Connie slams the front door - sound effect required)"
    # (BW turns to the boss)"
    show sc w3sowbk k19
    bw"Well I hope you‚Äôre proud of yourself."
    show sc w3sowbk k04
    tb"What did I do?"
    show sc w3sowbk k18
    bw"You‚Äôve upset your only daughter by putting yourself before anyone else, yet again!"
    show sc w3sowbk k28
    tb"Oh great, so you‚Äôre angry with me as well? Well that‚Äôs just fucking perfect!"
    show sc w3sowbk k19
    bw"Seriously, when are you going to start putting this family first?"
    show sc w3sowbk k29
    tb"Are you kidding me? Everything I‚Äôve done is for this family!"
    tb"None of you would have any of THIS if it wasn‚Äôt for me!"
    # (BW puts her hand up at the Bosses face)"
    show sc w3sowbk k18
    bw"I can‚Äôt listen to you anymore."
    bw"I‚Äôm going to find our daughter and hopefully I can fix up this huge mess that you‚Äôve made."
    show sc w3sowbk k04
    tb"Fine, go‚Ä¶."
    show sc w3sowbk k19
    bw"I‚Äôm telling you now that you better change that party to what Connie wants, do you hear me? Otherwise, your daughter may never forgive you."
    # (BW leaves) "
    show sc w3sowbk k33
    brod"Dad, how could you do that to Connie? And on her eighteenth birthday?"
    show sc w3sowbk k30
    tb"The hotel needed to regain some of the limelight back on it after the debacle of not getting that wedding that took place yesterday."
    tb"That was a huge financial miss for us son."
    show sc w3sowbk k31
    tb"But by having your sister‚Äôs eighteenth birthday party at my hotel, and more importantly in the penthouse suite..."
    show sc w3sowbk k34
    tb"It‚Äôs pretty much a guarantee that we will once again be the hotel that everyone will want to stay at in town."
    tb"Especially with what I have planned for Saturday night‚Ä¶"
    tb"I‚Äôm sure you‚Äôve already had a look at some of the things that I have booked for her party, right?"
    show sc w3sowbk k32
    brod"I have. Dad, the guest list also contains a lot of people that Connie doesn‚Äôt even know."
    show sc w3sowbk k33
    brod"And they‚Äôre all business associates of yours, aren‚Äôt they?"
    show sc w3sowbk k30
    tb"As I said to your sister Brodie, having her party at the hotel is the best thing from a business perspective."
    tb"And I‚Äôve invited a few of the town‚Äôs wealthiest investors, so it‚Äôs kind of a huge deal."
    show sc w3sowbk k34
    tb"Just think of how much money this could mean for us Brodie."
    tb"I mean, if I become the biggest hotel magnate that this town has ever seen, then think of what that means for you future son."
    tb"You just wait and see."
    show sc w3sowbk k32
    brod"(Sigh‚Ä¶)"
    brod"(Why doesn‚Äôt Dad listen to anyone?)"
    brod"(He only cares about his own opinion and his hotel. It‚Äôs like we‚Äôre always an afterthought.)"
    brod"(Oh man, I hope Connie is going to be okay‚Ä¶)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)







label lb_w3sow_sc_returns:
    #     Week 3 (SOW) Scene 11 - Shortcake returns and they both decide to go look for S
    scene sc w3sowcreturns c03
    with dissolve
    c"[y_name]!"
    if renpy.loadable("extras.animations") and persistent.v_anim_enabled:
        window hide
        scene wip_05_c_home  at tt_top
        pause
        window show
    else:
        show sc w3sowcreturns c03
    c"Hi!"
    scene sc w3sowcreturns c05
    show screen scr_rewards("sc w3sowcreturns c05b","v_rewards_c_30")
    c"What are you doing here?"
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc w3sowcreturns c01
    mc"Hey [c_name]. Your Mom let me in and I‚Äôve been waiting for you to return."
    mc"Uh, you haven‚Äôt seen or spoken to [s_name] today, have you?"
    show sc w3sowcreturns c02
    c"No, I can‚Äôt say that I have. How come?"
    show sc w3sowcreturns c01
    mc"Well, I haven‚Äôt seen her since last night and I‚Äôve been asking the people closest to [s_name] if they‚Äôve happened to seen her."
    mc"Jazmin, Ivy, and Lily haven‚Äôt seen her either. I also asked your Mom."
    show sc w3sowcreturns c02
    c"Oh boy‚Ä¶ I hope she‚Äôs okay. Have you tried calling her?"
    show sc w3sowcreturns c05
    mc"No, because she left her phone at the hotel."
    c"That‚Äôs so strange, and so unlike [s_name]."
    show sc w3sowcreturns c01
    c"I wonder why she would leave without saying anything?"
    mc"Yeah, I know."
    mc"I started looking for her in town with Jazmin, but I had to cut my search short when Lily asked if I could see her and Ivy at their office."
    show sc w3sowcreturns c05
    c"So, are you going to go back into town to look for [s_name]?"
    show sc w3sowcreturns c01
    mc"I was thinking about it, seeing as I don‚Äôt have any other ideas for where she could be at this point."
    show sc w3sowcreturns c04
    c"How about I come with you? I don‚Äôt have any plans, and it sounds like you could do with the help."
    show sc w3sowcreturns c03
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc w3sowcreturns c03","sc w3sowcreturns c03x","v_pt_image_index_w3_08")
    mc"Oh, that‚Äôd be great [c_name]!"
    c"Okay, I just have to use the bathroom and let my Mom know that I‚Äôm going with you."
    c"Give me a few minutes."
    mc"No problem."
    # (Cousin leaves the room)"
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom
    show sc w3sowcreturns c06
    mc"(It‚Äôs great that [c_name] is willing to help me find [s_name].)"
    mc"(Though I can‚Äôt shake this nagging suspicion that Ashley might know where [s_name] is, as strange as that seems‚Ä¶)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    scene sc w3sowcstreet c01
    with dissolve
    play ambient "sound effects/01/00/street_sounds_ambience.mp3" fadein 1.0
    mc"Okay, this seems like a good place to start looking for [s_name]."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c02
    c"You're right. Let's keep an eye out for her."
    # (Cousin and the MC walking together around the main shopping mall - be sure to change the background images here to show that they are moving)"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    c"So, how was the wedding reception? Did anything interesting happen?"
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ I don‚Äôt think it would be smart to tell [c_name] about what I got up to last night.)"
    mc"(If I were to tell her then I‚Äôm not sure what she would think of me.)"
    mc"Uh, well, Victoria was able to have a selfie with that singer, Melody I think."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c11
    c"Oh really? Damn, now I wish I stayed for the reception!"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c03
    c"Melody didn‚Äôt stay at the hotel overnight, did she?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    mc"I‚Äôm afraid not. She flew out on her private plane late last night, or so I heard."
    mc"So your Mom said that you had to run some errands for her this morning?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c08
    c"Yeah, I had to pick up a couple of things that she said she needed for work."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    c"So about [s_name], what was the last thing you two spoke about before you went to bed?"
    mc"Uh, why do ask?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c09
    c"I‚Äôm trying to gather a few ideas as to why she would leave the hotel without telling anyone."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    mc"Playing the role of detective now, are you?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c05
    c"Well, I really enjoy reading crime fiction novels, and ‚Äúwhodunit‚Äù type stories, haha!"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    mc"Hopefully whatever the explanation is for [s_name]‚Äôs disappearance isn‚Äôt anything like those novels!"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c06
    c"Oh, I didn‚Äôt mean-"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    mc"Haha, it‚Äôs okay [c_name]. I was just kidding."
    mc"But what I can tell you is that [s_name] and Ashley had a bit of an argument during the wedding reception."
    mc"That could‚Äôve played some part in [s_name] taking off without notifying anyone."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c09
    c"What did they argue about?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c03
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ I think I should tell [c_name] what I know. She seems pretty trustworthy and it kind of concerns her.)"
    mc"Well‚Ä¶ Ashley came to see [s_name] to tell her the real reason why they moved out from me and my father‚Äôs house nearly nine years ago."
    mc"The truth is, she caught my father fooling around with another woman."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c11
    c"Oh my god, he did?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c03
    mc"Yeah. Ashley told me this a couple of days ago because I was desperate to know the truth about why she left with [s_name] all those years ago."
    mc"This was the real reason why she moved out and took [s_name] with her."
    mc"She withheld the truth from [s_name] all this time because she wasn‚Äôt sure how she would take this news."
    mc"[s_name] was upset because Ashley didn‚Äôt tell her sooner, and for also keeping her from contacting me."
    mc"Ashley told me that she wasn‚Äôt sure how to tell [s_name], and feared how she would react."
    mc"I can understand her reasoning behind this now."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c09
    c"Oh [y_name]..."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c06
    c"So both your Dad and Ashley lied to you and [s_name]? I feel so bad for you both."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c03
    mc"It‚Äôs okay, don't feel sorry for us."
    mc"However, it seems like it‚Äôs affected [s_name] a lot worse than I thought it would."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c10
    c"So, did Ashley tell you who the woman was that your father was fooling around with?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    mc"No, she said she had no idea who she was."
    mc"She found some other woman‚Äôs lingerie in their car and something to do with late-night conversations that my father had with someone."
    # (Cousin places her hand on the MC‚Äôs shoulder)"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c10
    c"Have you spoken to your Dad about this?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    mc"No, not yet. I don‚Äôt how I‚Äôm going to, while also trying to keep my emotions in check."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c06
    c"That‚Äôs so unfair..."
    c"You and [s_name]‚Äôs lives could‚Äôve been so different if at least one of them had told you the truth sooner."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c03
    c"The two of you could‚Äôve been a great comfort to each other throughout your teenage years."
    # [Compliment her / Say nothing]"
    menu:
        "Compliment her"(wt="Best choice"):
            show sc w3sowcstreet c07
            mc"And you know what would have been even better?"
            c"No, what?"
            mc"I would‚Äôve met you a lot sooner. I never knew that [s_name] had a younger cousin."
            # (Cousin smiles)"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c08
            c"Well, we‚Äôre getting to know each other now, right?"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c04
            $ c_points = change_stat(c_points,2,c_name)
            mc"Yeah, for sure." #+2 COUSIN POINTS"
        "Say nothing":
            show sc w3sowcstreet c10
            # (scene continues)"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c10
    c"So, have you tried contacting my aunt Ashley?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    mc"Not yet. Your Mom told me that she‚Äôs working today, so that‚Äôs not an option right now."
    mc"It‚Äôs kind of a last resort for me at the moment."
    mc"I want us to try and find [s_name] without having to call Ashley."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c06
    c"I understand. You probably don‚Äôt want to worry Ashley by telling her that [s_name] is missing."
    mc"Yeah, exactly."
    # (MC notices most shops are running Father's Day offers)"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c03
    mc"So‚Ä¶ Your Mom was saying that you don‚Äôt normally do anything for Father‚Äôs Day."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c06
    c"No, no we don‚Äôt. I‚Äôd usually do something with [s_name] instead."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c03
    mc"Oh really? Trisha never told me that."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c06
    jump lb_w3sow_sc_returns_1

label lb_w3sow_sc_returns_1:
    c"She doesn‚Äôt know."
    c"I think me and [s_name] not knowing who our own fathers are has brought us closer together over the years."
    c"Rather than be depressed about it, we decided a few years back that we‚Äôd always do something special to celebrate it."
    jump lb_w3sow_sc_returns_2

label lb_w3sow_sc_returns_2:
    show sc w3sowcstreet c03
    mc"That‚Äôs very unusual, but it‚Äôs also great that the two of you have found a way to handle not having a Dad to celebrate the day with."
    mc"It‚Äôs actually quite admirable."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    mc"So what do you and [s_name] normally do to celebrate it?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c10
    c"Last year we just had a picnic on the beach."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c08
    c"Her attitude was that we don‚Äôt need a Dad or a father-figure to be happy, something I completely agree with."
    mc"Good for you."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    c"What about you?"
    c"I guess after what you found out about your Dad that you won‚Äôt be calling him on Father‚Äôs Day."
    mc"No, definitely not."
    mc"We rarely celebrated it anyway because he was usually away at sea around this time of year."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c04
    c"Well, how about this? When we find [s_name], maybe the three of us could celebrate it together?"
    mc"Really? I mean that‚Äôs nice and all, but I wouldn‚Äôt want to intrude on your tradition."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c05
    c"Not at all! I‚Äôd love for you to be there for it. I mean, we‚Äôd love you to be there."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c04
    mc"Okay, sure, count me in."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c12
    mc"I don't think [s_name] is around here."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c07
    c"Perhaps we should head towards the park and see if we can spot her over there?"
    mc"Okay, sounds good."
    # (MC and cousin are approached by a guy with a professional camera)"
    scene sc w3sowcstreet c13
    with dissolve
    mc"Okay, we'll spend some time here and see if we can find her."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c19
    show screen scr_rewards("sc w3sowcstreet c18b","v_rewards_c_31")
    pho"Excuse me guys, how you are both doing on this fine day?"
    mc"Uh, great thanks."
    pho"That‚Äôs good to hear."
    pho"I work for a local newspaper in town and they‚Äôve asked me to take some photos of locals enjoying their Sunday afternoon stroll through the Sunshine Bay mall."
    pho"The photos I take are to try and help entice more people to visit the many shops that they have in the centre."
    pho"Would you mind if I take a picture of you two together?"
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc w3sowcstreet c13
    mc"Sorry, who did you say you were with?"
    pho"I take photos for the Sunshine Bay Tribune."
    # [Agree / Disagree]"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c14
    menu:
        "Agree"(wt="Best choice"):
            $ v_w3sow_c_couple_photo = True
            show sc w3sowcstreet c13
            mc"Well in that case, sure, we‚Äôd love to. Are you okay with this [c_name]?"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c15
            if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
                show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc w3sowcstreet c15","sc w3sowcstreet c15x","v_pt_image_index_w3_09")
            c"Yeah, as long as you are."
            mc"Haha, of course."
            hide screen scr_peeping_tom
            show sc w3sowcstreet c20
            pho"Great!"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c13
            pho"I‚Äôll get you two to stand next to each other, please."
            show sc w3sowcstreet c21
            mc"How‚Äôs this?"
            pho"Yeah, however, you don‚Äôt have to pose like you‚Äôre in the army you two."
            show sc w3sowcstreet c22
            pho"How about you put your arm around her?"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c23
            c"(Oh!)"
            mc"Um, okay."
            # (MC nervously puts his arm around cousin)"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c24
            mc"How‚Äôs this?"
            pho"Yeah, but maybe you should try and relax guys. It‚Äôs only a photo, yet you both look so rigid."
            show sc w3sowcstreet c25
            c"(Sigh‚Ä¶)"
            c"(Why am I so nervous having [y_name]‚Äôs arm around me?)"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c26
            c"(He‚Äôs just doing what the guy asked him to. And this photo is meant to be fun.)"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c27
            mc"(Woah! [c_name] just put her arm around my waist!)"
            c"Is this better mister?"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c28
            if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
                show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc w3sowcstreet c28","sc w3sowcstreet c28x","v_pt_image_index_w3_10")
            pho"Yes, perfect! Now hold still, and‚Ä¶"
            # (Photo is taken)"
            play sound "sound effects/01/00/camera_phone_photo.mp3"
            pho"Done!"
            $ c_points = change_stat(c_points,3,c_name)
            pho"Lovely!" #+3 COUSIN POINTS"
            hide screen scr_peeping_tom
            show sc w3sowcstreet c22
            pho"Thank you so much for your time guys, that was perfect."
            show sc w3sowcstreet c18
            mc"So when will that be in your paper?"
            pho"It should be in the local guide section of our Wednesday bulletin, so make sure to grab yourself a copy."
            show sc w3sowcstreet c17
            c"We will."
            show sc w3sowcstreet c20
            pho"Okay, I better get going, as I have plenty of other couples to take photos of!"
            mc"(Couples?)"
            pho"Bye guys!"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c17
            c"Bye!"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c15
            c"Well, he seemed nice."
            mc"Yeah, he did."
        "Disagree":
            mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ That sounds like a made-up name.)"
            mc"(The skeptical side of me thinks that this guy will use a picture of me and [c_name] for other reasons.)"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c18
            mc"I‚Äôm sorry buddy, but we‚Äôre going to have to respectfully decline. So if you don‚Äôt mind?"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c19
            pho"No problem at all. Sorry to disturb you. Have a great day guys."
            # (Cousin looks at the MC, disappointed look on her face)"
            $ c_points = change_stat(c_points,-3,c_name)
            c"(Why did [y_name] say no to that guy? Was he too embarrassed to have a photo with me?)" #-3 COUSIN POINTS"
            show sc w3sowcstreet c14
            mc"(Why is [c_name] looking at me like that for? She didn‚Äôt actually want to have a photo with me, did she?)"
            # (scene continues)"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c14
    c"Uh, do you think we could maybe take a break and find somewhere to sit [y_name]?"
    c"I could do with something to drink as well."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c13
    mc"Yeah, of course we can."
    show sc w3sowcstreet c18
    mc"How about we go to that coffee shop over there?"
    show sc w3sowcstreet c15
    c"Perfect!"
    c"While we‚Äôre waiting for our orders, I could check [s_name]‚Äôs social media accounts to see if she‚Äôs posted anything."
    c"If she has, then maybe it will give us a clue as to where she is."
    mc"Good thinking‚Ä¶"
    stop ambient fadeout 1.0
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)




label lb_w3sow_mc_c_coffee:
    # Week 3 (SOW) Scene 12 - SC and MC stop at a coffee shop"
    scene sc w3sowccafe c01
    with dissolve
    play ambient "sound effects/02/01/restaurant_ambient_noise.mp3" fadein 1.0
    c"So you mentioned earlier that Ivy and Lily asked you to their office."
    c"What did they want?"
    mc"They wanted to discuss a few ideas that they feel will help improve things at the hotel."
