    show sc w3cpool c02
    mc"I think we have to."
    mc"Unless of course she really does have the money to pay for a party with that many people."
    mc"We‚Äôd have to get a down payment from her though."
    show sc w3cpool c01
    c"I could ask Connie if you want me to?"
    mc"Are you sure?"
    show sc w3cpool c04
    c"Yeah, I think she trusts me. And my gut feeling is she‚Äôs telling us the truth."
    # (Connie stands behind the MC and cousin and speaks up)"
    show sc w3cpool c15
    con"Excuse me, guys?"
    # (Cousin turns around)"
    show sc w3cpool c06
    c"Oh! You‚Äôre not on the phone with your Mom anymore?"
    show sc w3cpool c14
    con"No, I kept it short."
    show sc w3cpool c15
    con"She asked me to come home and I asked her if my father would change the venue, and he‚Äôs still refusing to do so."
    show sc w3cpool c06
    c"Oh‚Ä¶ So what are you going to do?"
    show sc w3cpool c10
    con"I don‚Äôt wanna go home, so I might find somewhere to stay in town for the night."
    show sc w3cpool c05
    c"Well, you could always stay here at the hotel if you wanted to?"
    mc"(What is [c_name] doing?)"
    show sc w3cpool c14
    con"Seriously?"
    show sc w3cpool c08
    c"Sure! As we said before, there‚Äôs plenty of vacant rooms."
    show sc w3cpool c01
    c"Isn‚Äôt there [y_name]?"
    mc"Uh, yeah, there is."
    mc"(I don‚Äôt know if they‚Äôve all been properly cleaned...)"
    mc"(Or what [s_name] would think if we let another person stay at the hotel without me discussing it with her first.)"
    show sc w3cpool c16
    mc"(Then again, she‚Äôs not here, and that leaves me in charge.)"
    con"That‚Äôs very nice of you both..."
    show sc w3cpool c15
    con"But I don‚Äôt have a change of clothes."
    show sc w3cpool c05
    c"Well‚Ä¶ Maybe you can borrow some of mine? Or one of [y_name]‚Äôs shirts while we run your clothes through the wash?"
    mc"(Eh?)"
    show sc w3cpool c11
    con"Are you sure I‚Äôm not putting you guys out?"
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ Having Connie stay at the hotel might help to convince her to have her party here.)"
    show sc w3cpool c10
    mc"No, not at all."
    mc"In fact, we might even have some clothes that you can wear that are in our lost and found section."
    mc"They‚Äôre mainly from previous guests that have left various things behind."
    show sc w3cpool c09
    con"Thanks for your generosity guys."
    show sc w3cpool c12
    con"In return, I‚Äôd like to buy you both dinner."
    show sc w3cpool c16
    con"Would you be interested in ordering some food to be delivered?"
    show sc w3cpool c08
    c"Yeah, definitely interested!"
    show sc w3cpool c02
    mc"So are you able to stay for dinner [c_name]?"
    show sc w3cpool c01
    c"I think my Mom would be okay with it. I‚Äôll give her a call shortly just to make sure."
    show sc w3cpool c09
    con"Then it‚Äôs settled. And it‚Äôs the least I could do, seeing as you both have been so nice to me."
    mc"(Offering to buy dinner for us? Well, that‚Äôs a good start.)"
    mc"(Maybe everything Connie has told us so far has been legit?)"
    mc"(I‚Äôll find out for sure once we all sit down to eat‚Ä¶)"
    stop ambient fadeout 1.0
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)





label lb_w3sow_mc_connie_night:
    # Week 3 (SOW)  Scene 14 - MC and Cousin put Connie up for the night in MC's room"
    scene sc w3cdinner d01
    with dissolve
    c"Thanks again for getting dinner Connie."
    show sc w3cdinner d05
    con"It was no trouble at all. How was the food?"
    show sc w3cdinner d12
    mc"It was wonderful. No, it was scrumptious!"
    show sc w3cdinner d09
    con"Haha! I‚Äôm so glad I ordered something you both liked."
    show sc w3cdinner d02
    c"Would you like some more wine Connie?"
    show sc w3cdinner d07
    con"Actually, do you think it would be okay if I took a shower?"
    show sc w3cdinner d10
    con"I haven‚Äôt had one since this morning and I‚Äôd really like to get out of these clothes."
    mc"Oh, of course you can."
    show sc w3cdinner d12
    con"And I was hoping that you could show me where I‚Äôll be sleeping tonight."
    mc"Sure, I can do that."
    show sc w3cdinner d02
    c"Are you going to rejoin us after your shower Connie?"
    show sc w3cdinner d07
    con"Um, I don‚Äôt want to sound rude, but I was thinking of having an early night guys."
    show sc w3cdinner d01
    c"No need to apologise. It‚Äôs been a hard day for you and it‚Äôs totally understandable."
    show sc w3cdinner d08
    con"But I‚Äôll see you tomorrow though, right?"
    show sc w3cdinner d01
    c"Yes, of course. I can come back in the morning to see you."
    show sc w3cdinner d03
    c"I‚Äôll probably head home soon [y_name]."
    mc"Will you be okay while I show Connie to her room [c_name]?"
    show sc w3cdinner d04
    c"Yeah, I‚Äôll be fine."
    show sc w3cdinner d01
    c"Goodnight Connie."
    show sc w3cdinner d05
    con"Night [c_name]. Thanks for everything today."
    show sc w3cdinner d01
    c"You‚Äôre welcome."
    show sc w3cdinner d04
    mc"I‚Äôll be right back‚Ä¶"
    # (Cousin smiles, sits on the sofa by herself)"
    # (screen goes blank)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    # (the MC and Connie walk to the hotel rooms)"
    scene sc w3cdinner d14
    with dissolve
    con"So how long have you been working at the hotel?"
    mc"Just a few weeks."
    show sc w3cdinner d17
    con"Really? And you‚Äôre already co-running this place?"
    show sc w3cdinner d15
    con"That seems kind of fast to be given such an important position."
    show sc w3cdinner d14
    mc"Well, I‚Äôm not actually from Sunshine Bay. I live in Darkham City."
    show sc w3cdinner d19
    c"Wow! You‚Äôre a long way from home then. So what brings you here?"
    show sc w3cdinner d14
    mc"You probably heard me and [c_name] mention the name [s_name] earlier on."
    jump lb_w3sow_mc_connie_night_1

label lb_w3sow_mc_connie_night_1:
    mc"She‚Äôs not only the co-owner of this hotel, but she‚Äôs also someone I‚Äôve known since I was a kid."


label lb_w3sow_mc_connie_night_2:
    show sc w3cdinner d13
    con"Oh, now I see the connection. So you two are pretty close then?"
    show sc w3cdinner d14
    mc"Yeah. Well, we weren‚Äôt always close."
    mc"We have been lately, but it‚Äôs hard to say what we are right now. "
    show sc w3cdinner d19
    con"You sound like you‚Äôre really worried about her."
    show sc w3cdinner d14
    mc"I am. But I know that she can take care of herself."
    mc"What about your folks? Won‚Äôt they be concerned that you‚Äôre not returning home to them tonight?"
    show sc w3cdinner d19
    con"I‚Äôm sure my Mom is worried but my Dad couldn‚Äôt care less about me."
    show sc w3cdinner d14
    con"He made that pretty clear this morning by not telling me the truth about my birthday party."
    show sc w3cdinner d17
    con"And he also sent me off to boarding school when I was twelve."
    mc"Boarding school? Really?"
    show sc w3cdinner d19
    con"Yeah, it's also a school just for girls. I wanted to go to a co-ed high school but he wouldn‚Äôt let me."
    show sc w3cdinner d15
    con"The last few years I only came home at Christmas and for my summer holidays."
    con"I have a really crappy father, hey?"
    mc"Yeah, it sounds like it. And believe me, I know all about crappy fathers."
    show sc w3cdinner d14
    con"Your Dad lied to you too?"
    mc"Yeah, and in a pretty bad way. It‚Äôs a very long story."
    mc"But I‚Äôve learned to not let it bother me, and to try and do what makes me happy, ultimately."
    mc"Do you know what I mean?"
    show sc w3cdinner d18
    con"Yeah, I‚Äôm pretty sure I do."
    show sc w3cdinner d13
    mc"(She seems really sweet. Connie doesn‚Äôt seem to be the type to be keeping any secrets.)"
    con"So which hotel room will I be staying in?"
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ The more I think about it, maybe putting Connie in one of the hotel rooms isn‚Äôt such a good idea.)"
    mc"(I don‚Äôt know if the staff that the twins supplied us with to clean the rooms were able to get around to all of them today.)"
    mc"(And it‚Äôs too late to ask them now.)"
    show sc w3cdinner d14
    mc"Um, on second thought, why don‚Äôt you take my room instead Connie?"
    show sc w3cdinner d19
    con"Huh? Why would I do that when you have all these vacant hotel rooms to choose from?"
    show sc w3cdinner d15
    mc"(Damn‚Ä¶ I knew she was going to ask me that.)"
    mc"(And I can‚Äôt seem to come up with a perfectly good lie to answer that. Or can I?)"
    show sc w3cdinner d17
    con"[y_name]? What‚Äôs the real reason you don‚Äôt want me to stay in one of your hotel rooms?"
    # [Truth / Be funny]"
    show sc w3cdinner d14
    menu:
        "Truth"(wt="Best choice"):
            mc"Look, here‚Äôs the truth Connie."
            mc"I mentioned [s_name] before, and, well, I haven‚Äôt seen or heard from her all day."
            mc"And even though she said that I‚Äôd be in charge whenever she‚Äôs not here..."
            mc"I‚Äôm not entirely sure if she‚Äôd be okay with me offering a hotel room to somebody she doesn‚Äôt know or hasn‚Äôt met."
            mc"So I figured that maybe you could stay in my room instead, and that way I could somewhat explain my actions if she happens to return tonight."
            mc"Sorry for not being honest with you from the beginning."
            mc"(I don't think I could ask her to pay for a room now, especially after we offered her to stay here for nothing.)"
            show sc w3cdinner d13
            $ connie_points = change_stat(connie_points,2,"Connie")
            con"It‚Äôs fine [y_name], I actually understand where you‚Äôre coming from." #+2 CONNIE POINTS"
            con"You just want to do the right thing by her."
            show sc w3cdinner d14
            con"But where are you going to sleep?"
            mc"I‚Äôll probably stay in [s_name]‚Äôs room tonight."
            mc"If she does come back then it‚Äôs better that it‚Äôs me sleeping in her bed, rather than you."
            show sc w3cdinner d13
            con"That makes sense."
        "Be funny":
            show sc w3cdinner d14
            mc"There is a rat. A BIG RAT!"
            mc"And it‚Äôs uh, it‚Äôs been terrorizing some of our hotel guests."
            show sc w3cdinner d18
            con"Haha, that‚Äôs your reason? You‚Äôre funny [y_name], but not that funny."
            show sc w3cdinner d13
            mc"(What the hell did I say that for?? Why on earth did I think that she would believe that ridiculous excuse?)"
            show sc w3cdinner d14
            con"Look, if it means that much to you for me to take your room [y_name], then I‚Äôll sleep in there tonight."
            mc"I think that would be best."
            con"But where are you going to sleep?"
            mc"I‚Äôll probably stay in [s_name]‚Äôs room tonight."
            mc"If she does come back then it‚Äôs better that I‚Äôm sleeping in her bed, rather than you."
            # (scene continues)"
    show sc w3cdinner d14
    mc"Anyway, let me take you to my room."
    # (screen goes blank)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    # (MC and Connie in his room)"
    scene sc w3cdinner d27
    with dissolve
    mc"So, this is it."
    show sc w3cdinner d21
    con"This is where you sleep?"
    mc"Yeah, is it okay?"
    show sc w3cdinner d26
    show screen scr_rewards("sc w3cdinner d26b","v_rewards_connie_2")
    con"Oh yeah, this will definitely do."
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc w3cdinner d21
    con"Are all of the rooms like this one?"
    mc"Come to think of it, I don‚Äôt think they are! Haha!"
    show sc w3cdinner d20
    mc"I also had the sheets changed this morning, so they‚Äôre nice and fresh."
    mc"And if you think this is good, you‚Äôre gonna love the view."
    mc"When you get up in the morning, go out to the window or the balcony. You can see the whole beach from there."
    show sc w3cdinner d23
    con"Oh, that sounds amazing!"
    show sc w3cdinner d21
    mc"I‚Äôll see if I can find you some clothes that you can change into and wear to bed."
    show sc w3cdinner d22
    con"Uh, you don‚Äôt have to do that [y_name]."
    show sc w3cdinner d24
    con"However, do you have a shirt I could borrow for the night?"
    show sc w3cdinner d21
    mc"You want to wear one of my shirts?"
    show sc w3cdinner d22
    con"Yeah, if that‚Äôs okay with you?"
    show sc w3cdinner d26
    con"I figure a shirt your size would act as a decent bed shirt for someone my size."
    con"That's all I would require."
    show sc w3cdinner d21
    mc"(Oh man‚Ä¶ It sounds like she took what [c_name] seriously about borrowing one of my shirts.)"
    mc"Sure, uh, I should have something you can wear in the top drawer over there."
    mc"There‚Äôs also a brand-new toothbrush in the bathroom that is still in its packaging that you can use. And there are some fresh towels as well."
    mc"And if you get hungry or thirsty in the middle of the night, there‚Äôs a vending machine downstairs that we just restocked the other day."
    show sc w3cdinner d20
    con"Thank you for everything today [y_name], truly."
    show sc w3cdinner d26
    con"It‚Äôs nice to meet someone that‚Äôs really easy to talk to like you and [c_name]."
    # (Connie kisses him on the cheek - short kiss sound effect)"
    show sc w3cdinner d35
    con"Mwah!"
    mc"(Oh, that was unexpected.)"
    show sc w3cdinner d20
    mc"Okay, well, I better go now as [c_name] is waiting for me, and she's probably wanting to go home."
    mc"I‚Äôll see you in the morning for breakfast."
    show sc w3cdinner d23
    con"You will. Night [y_name]."
    show sc w3cdinner d20
    mc"Night Connie‚Ä¶"
    # (final shot of Connie looking at the MC as he leaves)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)







label lb_w3sow_mc_c_pool:
    # Week 3 (SOW) Scene 15 - SC and MC watch TV together. SC falls asleep and MC carries SC to his bed"
    if _in_replay:
        if y_name == None:
            $ y_name = "MC"
        else:
            $ y_name = persistent.y_name

        if s_name == None:
            $ s_name = "S"
        else:
            $ s_name = persistent.s_name

        if c_name == None:
            $ c_name = "Shortcake"
        else:
            $ c_name = persistent.c_name

        show screen toprightmenu
        play music "music/01/2936-fliegen-by-sascha-ende.mp3"
    scene sc w3cdinner d28
    with dissolve
    c"So, how did it go? Did you find Connie a room okay?"
    # [Tell her the truth / Bend the truth]"
    menu:
        "Tell her the truth"(wt="Best choice"):
            mc"Yeah, I um, I decided that it would be best to put Connie up in my room tonight."
            show sc w3cdinner d30
            c"You did? Why? I thought the hotel had plenty of vacant rooms available?"
            show sc w3cdinner d28
            mc"There are, however..."
            mc"I had my doubts on whether [s_name] would be okay if someone she doesn‚Äôt know was staying in one of the hotel rooms..."
            mc"Especially as I haven‚Äôt charged her for staying."
            show sc w3cdinner d30
            c"Oh, I see. I guess that makes sense."
            show sc w3cdinner d33
            c"(That seems a little silly.)"
            c"(I mean, [s_name] put Jazmin up without charging her or discussing it with [y_name] first.)"
            show sc w3cdinner d32
            c"(How is this any different?)"
            show sc w3cdinner d34
            $ c_points = change_stat(c_points,2,c_name)
            c"(He did tell me the truth though, rather than keeping that to himself.)" #+2 COUSIN POINTS"
            show sc w3cdinner d33
            c"(But does [y_name] have a thing for Connie? Is that why he put her up in his guest room?)"
            c"(No, surely not. I mean, he only met her today!)"
            show sc w3cdinner d30
            c"So where are you going to sleep?"
            show sc w3cdinner d28
            mc"I thought I might sleep in [s_name]‚Äôs bed instead."
            mc"Or on the living room sofa. I don‚Äôt know."
            show sc w3cdinner d33
            c"(Hmm, it sounds like that‚Äôs what he‚Äôs going to do. But why is this still bothering me so much?)"
            c"(It just feels a little strange that Connie will be sleeping in [y_name]‚Äôs bed tonight.)"
        "Bend the truth":
            show sc w3cdinner d28
            mc"Yeah, I uh, I think she‚Äôll be very happy with the room I chose for her."
            mc"(I don‚Äôt know why, but I get the feeling that telling [c_name] that I put Connie up in my room wouldn‚Äôt come across well.)"
            mc"(She may think I have ulterior motives, even though I don‚Äôt.)"
            mc"(God, why am I acting so paranoid??)"
            mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ Maybe I should‚Äôve just put her in one of the hotel rooms as I originally planned...)"
            show sc w3cdinner d29
            c"That‚Äôs great, I‚Äôm sure she will too."
            # (scene continues)"
    show sc w3cdinner d28
    mc"Uh, would you like some more wine?"
    show sc w3cdinner d29
    c"Yes, that would be nice. However, it feels a little hot in here."
    show sc w3cdinner d28
    mc"Oh, would you like me to turn the air conditioning on?"
    show sc w3cdinner d29
    c"I had another idea in mind. Why don‚Äôt we go outside and sit by the pool?"
    mc"Hmm‚Ä¶ That sounds like a great idea."
    show sc w3cdinner d28
    mc"Perhaps we can discuss some ideas for Connie‚Äôs party while we‚Äôre out there?"
    show sc w3cdinner d31
    c"And perhaps draw some inspiration over some more wine?"
    show sc w3cdinner d29
    mc"Haha, something like that."
    c"Okay, let‚Äôs do that then‚Ä¶"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    # (scene returns with the MC and cousin walking out to the pool area, lit up slightly)"
    scene sc w3cpool c22
    with dissolve
    play ambient "sound effects/01/00/Night_Time_Sound_FX.mp3" fadein 1.0
    c"So uh, where should we sit?"
    # [Pool chairs / Feet in the pool]"
    show sc w3cpool c02
    menu:
        "Pool chairs":
            mc"Uh, how about we each lay in one of those pool chairs?"
            show sc w3cpool c01
            c"Um, as nice as that sounds, I think if I lay down, then I‚Äôll probably fall asleep."
            show sc w3cpool c23
            c"I have an idea. Maybe we can sit down with our feet in the pool?"
            show sc w3cpool c01
            mc"Sure, that‚Äôs a much better idea."
            show sc w3cpool c04
            c"I was starting to feel a little warm all over so having my feet in the pool should help to cool me down."
        "Feet in the pool"(wt="Best choice"):
            show sc w3cpool c02
            mc"I have an idea. Maybe we can sit down with our feet in the pool?"
            show sc w3cpool c04
            $ c_points = change_stat(c_points,2,c_name)
            c"That sounds really nice [y_name]."#+2 COUSIN POINTS"
            show sc w3cpool c01
            c"I was starting to feel a little warm all over so having my feet in the pool should help to cool me down."
            # (scene continues)"
    # (cousin removes her shoes - shot of her little feet)"
    # (Cousin dips her toe into the water)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    scene sc w3cpool c24
    show screen scr_rewards("sc w3cpool c24b","v_rewards_c_33")
    c"Oooh! It‚Äôs a little cool."
    mc"Well you know what they say? It‚Äôs all right, once you‚Äôre in!"
    hide screen scr_rewards
    show sc w3cpool c28
    c"Haha, do they?"
    show sc w3cpool c25
    mc"Yeah, or so I‚Äôve heard."
    show sc w3cpool c29
    c"So, I have a few things I wanna ask you [y_name]."
    show sc w3cpool c26
    mc"Sure, ask away!"
    show sc w3cpool c32
    c"Well, my questions may seem a little personal, so you don‚Äôt have to answer them if you don‚Äôt want to."
    show sc w3cpool c26
    mc"I‚Äôm sure whatever you ask shouldn‚Äôt be a problem for me to answer."
    show sc w3cpool c25
    c"Okay, well, I‚Äôll just ask a few questions together, and you just answer them one at a time, okay?"
    mc"Sounds good to me."
    show sc w3cpool c29
    if v_w2_nicole_open_relationship:
        # ‚ÄúAdd these lines if the player is on the open relationship path‚Äù"
        c"All right‚Ä¶ So what‚Äôs life like in the city you‚Äôre from? What has your relationship with Nicole been like so far?"
    else:
        # ‚ÄúAdd these lines if the player broke up with Nicole‚Äù"
        c"All right‚Ä¶ So what‚Äôs life like in the city you‚Äôre from? What was your relationship with Nicole like?"
    show sc w3cpool c32
    c"And uh, what‚Äôs the likelihood of you staying in Sunshine Bay permanently?"
    show sc w3cpool c27
    mc"Wow, those are some interesting, but tough questions."
    show sc w3cpool c26
    mc"Okay, let me see here."
    # [Darkham City / Nicole / The future]"
    # *NOTE: The player will ONLY get +3 COUSIN POINTS if they choose the ‚ÄúNicole‚Äù option first, just for something different."
    jump lb_w3sow_mc_c_pool_menu

label lb_w3sow_mc_c_pool_menu:
    if v_w3sow_mc_c_pool_city and  v_w3sow_mc_c_pool_nicole and v_w3sow_mc_c_pool_future:
        jump lb_w3sow_mc_c_pool_menu_ending
    menu:
        "Darkham City" if v_w3sow_mc_c_pool_city == False:
            $ v_w3sow_mc_c_pool_city = True
            show sc w3cpool c26
            mc"The city I‚Äôm from, Darkham City, well, it has its good points, however, it‚Äôs nothing like this place."
            mc"It rains a lot and I think the gloominess of the city reflects on a lot of the people who live there."
            mc"Plus crime has been up a lot over the past couple of years."
            mc"But despite how bad my hometown sounds, it has some positive things about it too. Namely the nightlife."
            show sc w3cpool c31
            mc"The restaurants are all pretty great, as are the clubs and bars."
            show sc w3cpool c26
            mc"It‚Äôs perfect for anyone in their twenties or early thirties."
            show sc w3cpool c32
            c"What about people like me, who are usually shy and find it hard to interact with others?"
            show sc w3cpool c26
            mc"Yeah, they have smaller restaurants with rooms for one or two people if required, for those who want a bit more privacy."
            mc"The parks are really quite peaceful, but only during the summertime."
            show sc w3cpool c31
            c"I‚Äôve never been to one of the big cities before. But I‚Äôd like to someday."
            # [Make her an offer / Say nothing]"
            show sc w3cpool c25
            menu:
                "Make her an offer"(wt="Best choice"):
                    show sc w3cpool c26
                    mc"Maybe I could take you to Darkham City some time?"
                    mc"Or uh, you could come to visit me after I return there?"
                    show sc w3cpool c28
                    c"Oh, I‚Äôd love that."
                    show sc w3cpool c31
                    $ c_points = change_stat(c_points,2,c_name)
                    c"I‚Äôd certainly be more interested to go if you were there." #+2 COUSIN POINTS"

                "Say nothing":
                    show sc w3cpool c26
                    # (scene continues)"
            show sc w3cpool c26
            c"So what would you say are the main differences between your home and Sunshine Bay?"
            mc"Oh man, where to start?"
            mc"Apart from the weather being much better here, there‚Äôs not a beach for miles, so there would be no need for you to bring your surfboard."
            show sc w3cpool c28
            c"Haha, no, but at least it would save me some money on airplane baggage costs. What else?"
            show sc w3cpool c26
            mc"Even though I‚Äôve done a lot of walking since I arrived here, it‚Äôs much easier to get around Sunshine Bay."
            mc"Everything is so close and very easy to get to. That‚Äôs not the case back home."
            mc"Traffic is a nightmare at the start of the day and also when you‚Äôre trying to leave work."
            mc"That doesn‚Äôt seem to be the case here."
            show sc w3cpool c29
