    # - THIS SCENE WILL RUN IF THE PLAYER IS NOT ON EITHER OF THE TWINS PATHS"
    # (scene starts with the MC in town, at the mall)"
    mc"(Okay, I‚Äôve got what I need from the store and some extra tools for when I start working on that service elevator with Mister Roshi.)"
    mc"(It sure would be nice to not be just an errand boy, and to be able to delegate these kinds of jobs to someone else instead!)"
    mc"(All right, I should head back to the hotel-)"
    play sound "sound effects/01/00/Cell_Phone_Ring_Sound_Effect.mp3" loop
    "(Phone ringing)"
    # (screen shows a pic of Ivy and lily with their names under the pic)"
    mc"(Oh, Ivy's calling me. I better answer this then, it could be important.)"
    # [Answer it]"
    stop sound
    # (*screen renders required for Ivy when she is talking in this scene)"
    mc"Hello, [y_name] speaking."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l27
    ivy"Hey [y_name], it‚Äôs Ivy. How are you?"
    mc"Yeah, I‚Äôm very well thank you. Yourself?"
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l29
    ivy"Pretty good. I was so full of energy that I was out of bed at six o‚Äôclock."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l27
    ivy"I went for an early morning jog and got a good sweat on."
    ivy"And now I‚Äôm at work and while things are a little quiet, I thought I would give you a call to see how you were."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l26
    ivy"So what are you up to?"
    mc"I‚Äôm just collecting a few things for the tasks that you and your sister set for me and [s_name] the other day."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l29
    ivy"That‚Äôs great to hear."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l26
    ivy"By the way, any word from [s_name]?"
    mc"No, still nothing, aside from a brief online chat we had the other night."
    mc"However, I think I might give her Mom a call, as she‚Äôs the person most likely to know where [s_name] could be."
    mc"Anyway, I thought I‚Äôd get a good head-start on the day and try to get a few jobs done before [s_name] returns."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l29
    ivy"That‚Äôs great [y_name]."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l27
    ivy"What‚Äôs even better is that despite [s_name]‚Äôs absence, you‚Äôre still keeping the business running as usual."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l26
    mc"Thanks, but you and your sister were also a big help the other day, by offering to watch the hotel for a few hours."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l27
    ivy"We like to assist where and when we can. Always go ‚Äúabove and beyond‚Äù as they say."
    ivy"Feel free to ask for our help again whenever you need it [y_name]."
    mc"I will. Thanks for the offer."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l28
    ivy"So, I know you‚Äôve been very busy the past few days..."
    ivy"Even more so because of [s_name] taking some time for herself..."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l26
    ivy"But have you come up with any ideas for events that could be hosted at the hotel?"
    mc"As a matter of fact, I have one in mind that I was hoping to discuss with you."
    mc"It‚Äôs a funny story of how it came about actually."
    mc"The other day, just after I met with you and Lily at your office, [c_name] and I went out looking for [s_name] that afternoon."
    mc"We stopped off at a coffee shop in town, and we spoke to a girl who was crying and upset with her parents."
    mc"Long story short, we spoke to this girl, Connie, and she told us that her eighteenth birthday is this Saturday..."
    mc"And that she would like to host it at our hotel, specifically in the pool area."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l29
    ivy"That‚Äôs wonderful [y_name]!"
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l26
    ivy"And this girl and her parents are good for the money to cover costs?"
    mc"Yeah, they are, however, there‚Äôs one drawback."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l28
    ivy"What is it?"
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l26
    mc"Connie doesn‚Äôt know that I‚Äôm aware of this yet, but I kind of figured out that her father is the guy who owns Seascape hotel."
    mc"He‚Äôs Brodie‚Äôs father."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l14
    ivy"Oh my God! So Connie would be Brodie‚Äôs sister then?"
    mc"It appears so, yes."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l26
    ivy"Does this girl have any idea that the hotel is co-owned by [s_name]?"
    mc"She does, but I get the impression that she has no idea who [s_name] is."
    mc"Connie said that she‚Äôs been going to some all-girls school for the past five years and she only returned home during Christmas and summer holidays."
    mc"And [s_name] told me that she and Brodie have been dating on and off for the past three years."
    mc"So it could be possible that the two of them have never crossed paths before."
    mc"So what do you think? Is hosting this girl‚Äôs party a bad idea?"
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l29
    ivy"On the contrary! I think it‚Äôs a brilliant idea!"
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l27
    mc"You do? How come?"
    ivy"Lily and I just received word from a friend who heard from another friend that Connie‚Äôs father was planning something major this Saturday night at his hotel..."
    ivy"But nothing more than that."
    ivy"Whatever he had in mind clearly had something to do with his daughter‚Äôs eighteenth birthday party this weekend."
    ivy"So what I‚Äôm thinking is, imagine how he‚Äôs going to feel if we were to steal this party from right under his nose?"
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l29
    ivy"It would make it even better because it‚Äôs his own daughter‚Äôs party!"
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l27
    mc"Wow, you‚Äôre really on board with this idea!"
    ivy"Oh yeah."
    ivy"As I said to you before [y_name], my sister and I are winners, and we hate losing at anything."
    ivy"Sometimes you have to play dirty to get where you need to be in industries like ours."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l26
    ivy"But there‚Äôs one thing I need to know‚Ä¶"
    ivy"Do you know where Connie is right now or if she‚Äôs told her parents about possibly having her party at your hotel?"
    mc"I can answer both questions."
    mc"Connie has been staying at the hotel the past few nights, and her parents don‚Äôt know that."
    mc"Nor are they aware that she wants to have her party there."
    mc"As far as Connie‚Äôs father knows, he still thinks that her party is still going ahead at his hotel and that Connie has been staying at a friend‚Äôs house"
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l27
    ivy"Perfect. Let him continue to think that."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l26
    mc"Connie has told some of her friends that a pool party is still happening..."
    mc"But the full details of the party including the location won‚Äôt be revealed until Friday night."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l27
    ivy"Oh that‚Äôs good."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l28
    ivy"Wow! She must really despise her father if she‚Äôs willing to have a party at your hotel instead of his, huh?"
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l26
    mc"Yeah, they had a huge argument about it apparently, which is kind of the reason why she‚Äôs been hiding from him by staying at our hotel."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l27
    ivy"Hmm‚Ä¶ Now it all makes sense."
    ivy"Whatever you‚Äôve said to this Connie girl was obviously something she wanted to hear."
    ivy"And given her family‚Äôs wealth, it‚Äôs safe to say that she‚Äôs good for the money."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l29
    ivy"Well done [y_name]!"
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l27
    mc"Haha, it was nothing."
    ivy"All right, I‚Äôll start drawing up some plans for Saturday when I get back to the office, including caterers, seating plans, decorations‚Ä¶"
    ivy"And then I‚Äôll email them to you later this afternoon."
    mc"Cool, sounds great."
    ivy"Be sure to call me if you need anything, and to keep me posted about this party on Saturday."
    ivy"I‚Äôll start making some calls when I get back to the office."
    mc"Sounds great Ivy. Bye."
    show sc w3mowlilylunch l29
    ivy"Bye [y_name]."
    # (call ends)"
    show sc w3mowtwlunch l00
    mc"(I should get my butt back to the hotel, and then decide what to do about [s_name] when I get there‚Ä¶)"
